org.hibernate.ogm.datastore.redis

Class RedisJsonDialect

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.spi.BaseGridDialect
      • org.hibernate.ogm.datastore.redis.AbstractRedisDialect
        • org.hibernate.ogm.datastore.redis.RedisJsonDialect
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, MultigetGridDialect, GridDialect, Service

    public class RedisJsonDialect
extends AbstractRedisDialect
implements MultigetGridDialect
    Stores tuples and associations inside Redis as JSON.

    Tuples are stored in Redis as a JSON serialization of a Entity object. Associations are stored in Redis obtained as a JSON serialization of a Association object either within the entity or external. See DocumentStoreProperties.ASSOCIATIONS_STORE on how to configure entity or external storage.

    Author:
    Mark Paluch

      • createAssociation

        public Association createAssociation(AssociationKey key,
                                     AssociationContext associationContext)
        Description copied from interface: GridDialect
        Creates a new (empty) association for storing the tuples representing the rows corresponding to the given key.

        Only invoked if the association does not yet exist in the datastore. Implementations should not perform a round-trip to the datastore but rather return a transient instance. The OGM engine will invoke GridDialect.insertOrUpdateAssociation(AssociationKey, Association, AssociationContext) subsequently.

        Specified by:
        createAssociation in interface GridDialect
        Parameters:
        key - Identifies the association
        associationContext - Contains additional information that might be used to create the association
        Returns:
        the created association

      • getTuples

        public List<Tuple> getTuples(EntityKey[] keys,
                             TupleContext tupleContext)
        Description copied from interface: MultigetGridDialect
        Return the list of tuples with the given columns for a given list of keys. The tuples must be returned in the same order as the keys. If a key has no matching record, set null to the list entry.

        All the keys provided will have the same EntityKeyMetadata. In other words they target the same "table".

        Specified by:
        getTuples in interface MultigetGridDialect
        Parameters:
        keys - The array of tuple identifier
        tupleContext - Contains additional information that might be used to create the tuples
        Returns:
        the list of tuples identified by the keys
